com.urlisit.siteswrapper.cloud.model

Class Site

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.urlisit.siteswrapper.cloud.model.Site
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    com.google.gwt.user.client.rpc.IsSerializable

    public class Site
extends java.lang.Object
implements com.google.gwt.user.client.rpc.IsSerializable
    Holds the persistent description of a web-app. Instances of Site are created and persisted to the data-store as the result of HTTP POST calls from Google Apps Scripts running in Google Docs to the Rest servlet in Google App Engine.
    Since:
    12-05-2012
    Version:
    1.0
    Author:
    Todd Url , url

      • setEmpty

        public void setEmpty(boolean empty)
        Indicates this instance of Site is not an accurate representation of the current configuration of the Site. This can happen when a new uncustomized version of the site is deployed, but the configuration has yet to be completed. For example, the site is installed but the configuration wizard has not been run. In this case (empty == true), the site object cannot be used and the configuration wizard should be called.
        Parameters:
        empty -

      • isEmpty

        public boolean isEmpty()
        Returns true if the Site object is empty, i.e., not an accurate reflection of the current configuration of the site. This condition can and should be tested for as in the following example usage; 
         Site site = Dao.getSite();
 if (site.isEmpty())
   doSomething(); // Log an error and call the configuration wizard
 else
   doSomethingElse()
        Returns:
        the boolean value of the empty field
